Henry SULLIVAN, Appellant, v. UNITED STATES of America, Appellee. No. 8867. Circuit Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. Dec. 5, 1938. Ayres K. Ross, of Austin, Tex., for appellant. W. R. Smith, Jr., U. S. Atty., and H. W„ Moursund and J. M. Burnett, Asst. U. S. Attys., all of San Antonio, Tex.

Before SIBLEY, HUTCHESON, and HOLMES, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

The judgment is affirmed.
